JOHANNESBURG – Democratic Alliance (DA) Gauteng south chairperson Khume Ramulifho has obtained a legal opinion that says Natasha Mazzone's appointment as second deputy federal chairperson is invalid. Ramulifho, who unsuccessfully contested the position, lodged a complaint with the DA after the party's national congress in April. READ: DA certain it will reach agreement in appointment of Natasha Mazzone He says the legal opinion he sought has found Mazzone's appointment to be invalid. “The federal executive has to deliberate on the matter and they will be meeting this Friday and Saturday.  So I will only take this matter [on] after that because for now, I have just shared the opinion which I have received.” eNCA